Reviewed **`src/blog/people/drafts/David-Beckham.md`** with fresh eyes and appended a `FRESH EYES REVIEW (2026-07-13)` block at the bottom (no body edits, per the command).

This draft is genuinely strong — the 1998 crisis section, the 2am inner-thought paragraph, and the honest Qatar critic pressure are all doing real work. So the notes are mostly about two blind spots rather than a rescue job.

**The two biggest issues I flagged:**

1. **The Brooklyn estrangement is missing — and it breaks the ending.** As of 2026 Beckham's firstborn has publicly accused his parents of "prioritizing the family brand over personal relationships" and said he doesn't want to reconcile. That is *word-for-word* the Type 3 shadow this draft describes ("A Three builds a trophy and then needs the trophy to be true"). But the piece resolves the family theme warmly and crowns the family-man arc as if it's still 2024. It's simultaneously the sharpest live critic pressure available and a direct hit on the thesis — and it's absent.

2. **The flying-boot incident (Feb 2003) is absent**, so the timeline jumps to "Ferguson sells him to Real Madrid" with no cause. The boot-over-the-eye moment — plus Beckham reportedly showing up next day with hair swept back to display the stitches to the paparazzi — is peak Type-3 image management and belongs in "brand out of a haircut."

Also noted: expand Victoria as co-architect (not just affair-survivor), add the England captaincy to the redemption arc, trim the back-to-back candle/fridge repetition in the childhood section, and cash out or cut the unexplained "agent he was told not to hire" reference.

